Subject: BOGUS privilege error during client installation
Description:
Receiving the follow error during version 6.2.3.1 installation under ADMINISTRATOR account:

Service 'Endpoint Protector' could not be installed. Verify that you have sufficient privileges to install system services.
What_We_Know__c:
the customer migrated and needed to update the agent, so they manually installed it over the old one, but the IP was populated wrong.
I sent the disclaimer and provided the zap tool, and they will manage to install it on all computers.
Since it is a fresh server, they will need a new license file, but now it is still OFFLINE.
Next_Steps__c: monitoring and will do a check next week.
Solution_Comment__c: agents installed without issues after a remote session
